H0.text: An ovary is where an angiosperm seed develops inside.

H1.text: Fallopian tubes are the location inside which an angiosperm seed develops.

H2.text: A kidney is the structure inside of which an angiosperm seed develops.

H3.text: The pancreas is where an angiosperm seed develops.

A4.text: In flowering plants, an ovary is a part of the female reproductive organ of the flower or gynoecium.

A5.text: the ovules inside the ovary become the seeds of that fruit.
